# Multi-agent Git worktrees (required)

When more than one agent (or agent + human) working in parallel, **do not share one working tree**. Use `git worktree` so each agent has its own working directory and index.

## Rules

- **One agent = one worktree + one branch**.
- **No committing from primary repo dir** (`/Users/parv3213/Documents/habbit-tracker`) when multiple agents active.
- **No `git add .`** in multi-agent mode. Stage explicit paths only.
- Avoid disruptive commands in shared context: `checkout` to other branches, `reset --hard`, `stash`, interactive rebases.

## Standard setup (from repo root)

```bash
git worktree list
git worktree add ../habbit-tracker-agent1 -b agent1-work main
git worktree add ../habbit-tracker-agent2 -b agent2-work main
```

## Standard commit flow (inside agent worktree)

```bash
git status
git diff
git add <paths...>
git commit -m "..."
```

## Cleanup

```bash
git worktree list
git worktree remove ../habbit-tracker-agent1
git worktree remove ../habbit-tracker-agent2
```
